column5: Anybody been up Highway502 this year--road conditions and delays?? Has anybody fished Gullrock this year??

I was at Gullrock last week. No delays going up and the roads are fine. On the way back they were replacing a few culverts across the road in 3 spots but no biggie.Fishing was awesome as always. The 18 inchers were a tough find, but the overs were everywhere.............and I mean everywhere. More 25 inch plus fish as I've seen in 17 straight years there.
Thanks Johnboat--Leaving early Saturday.Looking forward to another great trip to Gullrock.
I'm sure you'll have a great week. Travel safe.
going to wright's in sept. have not been in 3 years but cant wait as we have fished out of Lee's place on gullrock the past 15 years or so. gullrock is a great lake.
